{
  "answer": "**Iqbal's precise opening line of the poem in *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 1 (\"Ajab waa'iz ki deen-daari hai ya Rabb\") is: \"عجب واعظ کی دینداری ہے یا رب\".**[^1]\n\nThis is the first line of the ghazal as presented in the original Urdu text.[^2] In poetic layout, it appears line-broken across two paragraphs, but the full opening couplet (matla) reads continuously as above.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 1 (\"Ajab waa'iz ki deen-daari hai ya Rabb\"), [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/01-ajab-waaiz-ki-deen-daari-hai-ya-rabb/original/#p-511fa1).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 1, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/01-ajab-waaiz-ki-deen-daari-hai-ya-rabb/original/#p-7d3094).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 1, [full chapter](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/01-ajab-waaiz-ki-deen-daari-hai-ya-rabb/original/).",
